{"lemma":"شَقِيقَةٌ","slug":"شَقِيقَةٌ","root":"ش.ق.ق","root_slug":"ش-ق-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ق-ق","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22708"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"female equivalent of شَقِيق (šaqīq): full sister","tags":["feminine","form-of"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"migraine"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ellipsis of شَقِيقَة النُّعْمَان (šaqīqa(t) an-nuʕmān)","tags":["abbreviation","alt-of","ellipsis"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"feminine singular of شَقِيق (šaqīq)","tags":["feminine","form-of","singular"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22708","headword_ar":"شَقِيقَةٌ","root":"$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[accord. to Golius,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A fissure;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as from the KL; but not so expl. in my copy of that work. ―         -b2- ]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An intervening space"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract between two elongated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended, tracts of sand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * O, K, * [in the last of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljabalayoni","text_ar":"الجَبَلَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljabolayoni","text_ar":"الجَبْلَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) thus expl. to AHn by an Arab of the desert, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"producing herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a rugged tract between two elongated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended, tracts of sand, producing good herbage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA;) so in the T, as expl. to its author by an Arab of the desert: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"شَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (T, S, O, K, TA,) expl. by some as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sands"},{"kind":"text","text":"themselves: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great piece of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of sand between two pieces thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 282.) ―         -b3-  [In the A and TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiT~u","text_ar":"قِطُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", it is used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A slice cut off"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a melon &c.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a violent rain, consisting of large drops,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wide in extent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called because the clouds cleave asunder from it: (M, K, TA:) pl. as above. (TA.) ―         -b2-  The pl.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAy^iqu","text_ar":"شَقَايِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is expl. by Az as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds that have cloven asunder with copious rains."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqapu baroqKi","text_ar":"شَقِيقَةُ بَرْقٍِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqiyqatuhu","text_ar":"عَقِيقَتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", both as expl. by Aboo-Sa'eed, (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A flash of lightning that has spread"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the horizon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the horizon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K: [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqu","text_ar":"شَقِيقُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Albaroqi","text_ar":"البَرْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqapN","text_ar":"شَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flash of lightning that has spread in the breadth of the clouds, and filled the sky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (Ham p. 557.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A headache,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, T, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain disease,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the half of the head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, T, S, M, O, K,) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hemicrania,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the face:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, T, S, O, K:) or, accord. to IAth,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sort of headache in the fore part of the head and towards the sides thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAy^iqu Aln~uEomaAni","text_ar":"شَقَايِقُ النُّعْمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", used alike as sing. and pl., (S, O, K,) having no proper sing., (Msb,) or its sing. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqapN","text_ar":"شَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, O, Msb;) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"blood-coloured, anemone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain red flower;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqir","text_ar":"شَقِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or, as AHn says, on the authority of AA and Aboo-Nasr and others, it is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqirap","text_ar":"شَقِرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqirN","text_ar":"شَقِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and the sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$qAy^q","text_ar":"شقايق"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqapN","text_ar":"شَقِيقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, TA:) it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$qAy^q AlnEmAn","text_ar":"شقايق النعمان"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of its redness, as being likened to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiyqap","text_ar":"شَقِيقَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of lightning: (M, K:) or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uEomaAn","text_ar":"النُّعْمَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning “ blood, ” as resembling blood in colour; (Msb, TA;) so that it signifies “ pieces of blood: ” (TA:) or in relation to En-Noamán Ibn-El-Mundhir, because he prohibited to the public a piece of land in which it abounded: (S, K, TA:) or because he alighted upon"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAy^iq","text_ar":"شَقَايِق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sand that had produced red"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqir","text_ar":"شَقِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", and he deemed them beautiful, and commanded that they should be prohibited to the public; so the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqir","text_ar":"شَقِر"},{"kind":"text","text":"were called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$qAy^q","text_ar":"شقايق"},{"kind":"text","text":"of En-Noamán, by the name of the place of their growth. (TA.)       -A5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aquwqapN","text_ar":"شَقُوقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["TA","S","M","O","K","T","JK","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}